uk.ac.ebi.uniprot.dataservice.client.uniparc

Interface UniParcService

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Service

    public interface UniParcService
extends Service
    Service that queries the search engine, returning the UniParc entries that meet the search criteria. 
     // Create UniParc query service
  ServiceFactory serviceFactoryInstance = Client.getServiceFactoryInstance();
  UniParcService uniParcService = serviceFactoryInstance.getUniParcQueryService();

 // Example1: get entries with protein name "ClpC"

 Query query = UniParcQueryBuilder.proteinName("ClpC");

 QueryResult<UniParcEntry> entryIterator = uniParcService.getEntries(query);


 while(entryIterator.hasNext()) {
   UniParcEntry uniparcEntry = entryIterator.next();
   System.out.println("UniParc id = " +
                uniParcEntry.getUniParcId().getValue());

 }
 // Example2: get UniParc entry from UniProt accession: "T0LP84"

    String accession = "T0LP84";
    UniParcEntry entry = uniParcService.getEntryFromUniProtAccession(accession);
 ...

      • getEntries

        QueryResult<UniParcEntry> getEntries(Query request)
                              throws ServiceException
        Given a query, returns all UniParc matching the selection criteria of the query. 
          // Example1: get entries with protein name "ClpC"
  Query query = UniParcQueryBuilder.proteinName("ClpC");
  QueryResult<UniParcEntry> entries = uniParcService.getEntries(query);
        Parameters:
        request - Query containing the filter criteria
        Returns:
        a QueryResult of UniParc entries
        Throws:
        ServiceException - is thrown when there is a problem obtaining the entries from the search engine

      • getEntry

        UniParcEntry getEntry(String id)
               throws ServiceException
        Returns a UniParc entry for UniParc identifier. 
          // Example1: get an entry with UniParc identifier: UPI0000000001
  UniParcEntry entry = uniParcService.getEntry("UPI0000000001");
        Parameters:
        id - UniParc identifier
        Returns:
        The UniParcEntry that matches the given UniParc identifier or null if no entry is found
        Throws:
        ServiceException - is thrown when there is a problem obtaining the entries from the search engine

      • getSequences

        QueryResult<UniParcComponent<Sequence>> getSequences(Query query)
                                              throws ServiceException
        Given a Query, return an QueryResult of type UniParcComponent on Sequences, representing the sequence of every UniParc entry hit by the query. 
         // Example: get all UniParc sequences, that contain the organism name Homo
 // sapiens, in at least one of the active cross-references
 Query query = UniParcQueryBuilder.organismName("Homo sapiens");
 QueryResult<UniParcComponent<Sequence>> sequences = uniParcService.getSequences(query);
        Parameters:
        query - the query to be executed over UniParc data
        Returns:
        an QueryResult of UniParcComponents on type Sequence
        Throws:
        ServiceException - is thrown when there is a problem obtaining the entries from the search engine
